@node intro "Why should you use FW_Sessions?"
@{fg  shine}
                                  -----
                                  INTRO
                                  -----
@{fg text}

Have you ever heard about that little word "session"? And have  you  ever
thought about implementing this in your wordprocessor "FinalWriter"?

No? - Okay! Forget reading any further!

And now to those of you who know something about it.

Let me explain it with an example:

You have got this lovely piece of software (FW) on  your  Amiga  and  you
want  to  write very much and it will take days and days to be completed.
After  every  session,  you're  saving   your   document   and   quitting
FinalWriter.

After a day (or two) you want to write a bit more.  Your  steps  will  be
some of the following:

  - starting FinalWriter
  - opening the filerequester
  - trying to find the right directory and after it searching for the
    right file.
  - opening the document
  - jumping to the right part, the right page and the right paragraph of
    your document
  - and so on

As you can see, it is the same day by day by day. Wouldn't it be  better,
if  you  could  press just a little button of your toolmanager-dock which
will do this job for you? - I think so.

@endnode

@node discl   "What you see is what you get!"
@{fg shine}
