But: You are using FWSession on your own risk!

If you find any bugs or have any suggestions, please report them.


@endnode

@node overview "What is FW_Sessions?"
@{fg shine}
                                --------
                                OVERVIEW
                                --------
@{fg text}

FW_Session is a set of ARexx scripts which makes it possible to  load  and
save sessions.

If you save a document via FW_SaveSession you will quickly have access  to
this document and the last position of your work.

@endnode

@node contents "That's what you get"
@{fg shine}
                                 --------
                                 CONTENTS
                                 --------
@{fg text}

You will get two ARexx scripts and one shell-script, called:

          FW_LoadSession.rexx       -     Install this in your FW-Menu
          FW_SaveSession.rexx       -                 "
          Final_Last                -     A shell-script, that tries to
                                          load FinalWriter and calls the
                                          FW_LoadSession script.
                                          This is machine-generated by the
                                          Installer.

To work with this scripts,  you  have  to  have  the  rexxreqtools.library
installed on your system. This library is included.


@{fg fill}Which is which?
---------------@{fg text}

@{b}1) FW_LoadSession.rexx@{ub}

This  script  loads  the  last  or  an  alternate   session,   reads   the
corresponding document and jumps directly to the last edited paragraph.


@{b}2) FW_SaveSession.rexx@{ub}

Saves the actual document as  default  or  as  an  alternate  session  and
includes  several  informations  about  the  last edited paragraph and the
current cursor positions.


@{b}3) Final_Last@{ub}

This is a machine-generated shell script that calls FinalWriter  and  then
the FW_LoadSession.rexx script.


@endnode

@node install  "That's how to install FW_Sessions"
@{fg shine}
                               ------------
                               INSTALLATION
                               ------------
@{fg text}

To install FW_Sessions doubleclick the installer icon. You are now be able
to  choose  different directories where the script should move the scripts
to.

@{i}@{fg shine}
Note: You should use the installer to install FW_Sessions, because at this
point there will be created a shell script which is very, very usefull.
@{ui}@{fg text}

@endnode

@node usage    "That's how you have to use FW_Sessions"
@{fg shine}
                                 -------
                                  USAGE
                                 -------
@{fg text}

New in this version of FWSessions  is  that  every  script  "knows"  which
session  were  at  last  be accessed. To implement this feature, I have to
include a new ENV-Variable (FWSession/LAST) which holds the actual name of
the current session.

Further more you must not know the name of the last session just like the
last version of FWSession, because its name will simply be printed in the
requester body.

And now to the arexx-scripts:

@{fg fill}@{b}
1) FW_SaveSession
-----------------
@{fg text}@{ub}
This script opens a window where the user can choose to save  the  current
document  wether  as  the  same name as the last session or as an alterate
one.

If there is no "last session", the script opens  a  filerequester  without
any  asking.  This is something that should allready be implemented in the
last release of FWSession.

If you save  your  document  with  an  alternate  name,  the  ENV-Variable
FWSession/LAST  will be changed, so that FW_LoadSession gets access to the
new name.

@{fg fill}@{b}
2) FW_LoadSession
-----------------
@{fg text}@{ub}
If you call FW_LoadSession, you will be asked if you want to get the  last
or an alternate session.

If there is no "last session", the script opens  a  filerequester  without
any asking.

If  you  load  a  document  with  an  alternate  name,  the   ENV-Variable
FWSession/LAST will be updated immediatly.

@{fg fill}@{b}
3) Final_Last
-------------
@{ub}@{fg text}
This  machine-generated  script  starts  FW  and  loads  the  last  edited
document.

@endnode

@node history "A long, long time ago, that was very, very wrong"
@{fg shine}
                                -----------
                                THE HISTORY
                                -----------
@{fg text}

0.5 (01.04.97)        First private release.
                      You were only be able, to load/save one session, called
                      default.ses

1.0 (23.04.97)        Second private release.
                      You can now save several sessions. Created a filerequester,
                      where you can select the session, you will work with.

1.1 (09.07.97)        First public release.
                      Several bugfixes.
                      Created installer script and english version of the scripts.

1.2 (02.09.97)        + Second public release.
                      + Fixed one serious bug in FW_LoadSession.rexx
                      + Created the english version of this guide
                      + After a long period of writing, I find it usefull to know, what
                        session you want to load.
                        Now you are able to load a session and FW_LoadSession remembers
                        the name of the session.
                        You are able to save a session under a different name as loaded
                        and FW_SaveSession will remember the name, too.
                      + Changed the <Wait 4> command in Final_Last to an more multi-
                        tasking friendliy <WaitForPort FINALW.1>
                        (Days ago, I found it somewhere in my REXX: drawer...)
                      + FW_SaveSession will ask the user to save the document first

@endnode

